      "writtenOn": "2026-06-03T10:35:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m trying to understand what\u0027s the purpose of this enum.\nIs there an expectation for the future to have a different state from active/inactive?\nIf no, then this could be a boolean flag.\nIf yes - what would that be? ADMIN_DOWN maybe? I think CLI already prints something like that, maybe we could return it here too in a consistent way?",
      "revId": "8fa4800559150931da2de53c96858f02b9ae0734",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4c6dc6d5_2508a3b9",
        "filename": "src/plugins/lldp/lldp.api",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 102,
      "author": {
        "id": 2792
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-05T19:35:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I have no expectations for there to be additional states in the future, nor do I have expectations that there won\u0027t be additional states.  I thought it would be best to allow for the possibility, as well as giving the caller a named value to check for.\nThe value of the \"status\" field is determined the same way it is determined by the CLI.\nI\u0027ll change this to a boolean if you want.  I assume the field name should then be changed from \"status\" to something like \"active\".  That would allow it to make sense when checking the field value without having an enum to check against.\n\n(Added)  I\u0027ve made the change to using a boolean.",
      "parentUuid": "c4835447_a44eb800",
      "revId": "8fa4800559150931da2de53c96858f02b9ae0734",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
    },
